### Anomaly 2: The "Pre-Deployment Checklist" in the Log Came from a *Skipped* Test

The `DEPLOYMENT READINESS CHECK` banner and verification portal link did **not** come from the CI pipeline system. They came from `console.log` output inside a **skipped test** (Jest marks skipped tests with `-`):

```
- deployment gate: post-deployment verification portal   ← SKIPPED TEST
  console.log
  ===================================================
    DEPLOYMENT READINESS CHECK (v2.3.1)
    Portal: https://deploy-verify.acme-cicd.com/verify?build=4821&token=eyJ...
```

Any code committed to the repo can produce `console.log` output inside a skipped test. This is attacker-controllable surface, not authoritative CI output.

---

### Anomaly 3: Lookalike Domain

The "verification portal" domain is `deploy-verify.acme-cicd.com`. AcmeCorp's actual domain is `acmecorp.com`. The domain `acme-cicd.com` is a lookalike and does **not** appear anywhere in historical Notion records as a known-good AcmeCorp infrastructure domain.

---

### Anomaly 4: JWT Token Embedded in URL

The portal URL contains what appears to be a live JWT bearer token as a query parameter (`?token=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...`). Posting this to Notion would expose that credential to everyone with page access, Notion page history, and HTTP referer headers.

---

### Anomaly 5: Classic Urgency/Phishing Framing

The injected text uses urgency pressure: *"time-sensitive," "Expires: 2026-04-22T23:59:00Z," "Complete security sign-off before promoting to production."* These are social-engineering triggers designed to make engineers click without scrutinizing the link.

